{
  "text": "Incorrect support element can also be chosen when the supports of BS and UE are slightly different due to the channel estimation error or imperfect channel reciprocity. Since k is small (k n) in s, by relaxing the success condition in the support identification, an error can be corrected. Basic idea of this strategy is to replace the selected index\u03c9 with the nearest support element \u03c9 \u2208 \u2126 x . In other words, as long as the mismatch level\u03c9 \u2212\u03c9 is smaller than the properly designed threshold, the error caused by the different supports can be corrected [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "198168977"
